9. A single to differential interface, comprising: 
a single ended source that emits a single ended source output; 
a single to differential interface circuitry that is operable to convert the single ended source output to a pair of differential outputs; 
a differential receiver that receives the pair of differential outputs; and 
the single to differential interface circuitry employs a transmission-like connection between the single ended source and the differential receiver.

16. A single to differential interface method, comprising: 
referencing a single ended source output signal to a floating single ended source ground; 
implementing a differential interface that is referenced to a system ground; 
referencing a plurality of differential signals to a plurality of receiver power supply voltages; and 
connecting a first isolated power and ground plane to a second isolated power and ground plane via a transmission-like connection.
